\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Representative subgraph of the final Tier-1 knowledge graph, showing 20 nodes and 19 edges selected to illustrate the diversity of relation types extracted by the pipeline. Node color encodes entity type: blue = \texttt  {\small  SeismicObject}, orange = \texttt  {\small  Process}, green = \texttt  {\small  Descriptor}, purple = \texttt  {\small  Setting}. Edge color and abbreviated label encode relation type: \texttt  {hD} = \texttt  {\small  hasDescriptor}, \texttt  {oI} = \texttt  {\small  occursIn}, \texttt  {ca} = \texttt  {\small  causes}, \texttt  {tr} = \texttt  {\small  triggers}, \texttt  {pO} = \texttt  {\small  partOf}. The subgraph illustrates three structural components of the extracted knowledge: a causal chain linking \emph  {earthquake} and \emph  {growth stratal wedge} to \emph  {mass transport deposit} via slope failure; a set of seismic descriptors (\emph  {transparent}, \emph  {hummocky}, \emph  {high-amplitude}, \emph  {blocky}, \emph  {continuous}) directly attributed to the MTD; and depositional context relations linking the MTD to \emph  {continental margin} and \emph  {deepwater basinal setting}. Every edge is a Tier-1 triple verified against a source passage from the 41-paper corpus. The complete Tier-1 graph contains 101 triples across nine relation types.}}{15}{figure.caption.25}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:kg-subgraph}{{2}{15}{Representative subgraph of the final Tier-1 knowledge graph, showing 20 nodes and 19 edges selected to illustrate the diversity of relation types extracted by the pipeline. Node color encodes entity type: blue = \pred {SeismicObject}, orange = \pred {Process}, green = \pred {Descriptor}, purple = \pred {Setting}. Edge color and abbreviated label encode relation type: \texttt {hD} = \pred {hasDescriptor}, \texttt {oI} = \pred {occursIn}, \texttt {ca} = \pred {causes}, \texttt {tr} = \pred {triggers}, \texttt {pO} = \pred {partOf}. The subgraph illustrates three structural components of the extracted knowledge: a causal chain linking \emph {earthquake} and \emph {growth stratal wedge} to \emph {mass transport deposit} via slope failure; a set of seismic descriptors (\emph {transparent}, \emph {hummocky}, \emph {high-amplitude}, \emph {blocky}, \emph {continuous}) directly attributed to the MTD; and depositional context relations linking the MTD to \emph {continental margin} and \emph {deepwater basinal setting}. Every edge is a Tier-1 triple verified against a source passage from the 41-paper corpus. The complete Tier-1 graph contains 101 triples across nine relation types}{figure.caption.25}{}}
